title: H.S. cross-country: Around the course
text:
H.S. cross-country: Around the course October 9, 2015 Last updated: Friday, October 9, 2015, 1:21 AM Herald News Print 
Cross-Country: Around the course 
* Lakeland, North Arlington, Passaic Tech and Ramapo are entered in this afternoon’s Greystone Invitational at the Greystone course in Central Park in Parsippany. The varsity races begin at 4:30 p.m. and include small and large school races. 
* Early Saturday morning, the Garret Invitational at Garret Mountain will be held for the third time — with varsity races scheduled between 10:05 and 10:55 a.m. More than a dozen North Jersey teams are entered, but whether teams will run their full varsity or not is unclear. 
* IHA and Bergen Catholic are racing this afternoon at 4:15 and 5 pm at the Disney Cross-Country Classic on the grounds of the ESPN Wide World of Sports in Kissimmee, Florida. 
* Several teams will race in the Manhattan Invitational, traditionally the largest meet in the nation Saturday at Van Cortlandt Park in the Bronx. Don Bosco and River Dell will run in the Boys Eastern States Championship race held at 2:10 p.m. with Colin and Will Daly making their seasonal major meet debut for River Dell. Teaneck is entered in boys (12:58 p.m.) and girls (3:34 p.m.) varsity races with Hackensack and Bergen Tech in the boys (1:34 p.m.), Pascack Hills in the girls (3:57 p.m.) and Bergen Tech in the girls (4:10 p.m.). All-North Jersey star Michelle Kubasek is expected to make her seasonal major debut in the latter race.
